main event: A white and silver object with an oblong shape appeared at Fallon Navy Station, Nevada, observed through binoculars.
interesting points: The object was estimated to be at an altitude of 20,000 ft and traveling at a speed of 1,000 mph,The object had knobs on its surface and two ragged bumps in front,The sighting lasted for 25 seconds,The observation concludes that the object was probably an aircraft undergoing testing,The sighting occurred on 6 August 1956 at 052108Z GMT.
sighted object: one white and silver oblong object
